              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "AsWFO",
                  "fill": "#DC2626",
                  "content": "PHASE 01  ·  START THE LONG SIMMERS",
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 11,
                  "fontWeight": "700",
                  "letterSpacing": 1.6
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "yKGIa",
                  "fill": "#64748B",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "These run unattended for 30–60 min. Get them on the stove first.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.5,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 12,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "mgXfb",
                  "name": "ph1s1",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "gap": 14,
                  "padding": [
                    6,
                    0,
                    0,
                    0
                  ],
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "W0bS5",
                      "fill": "#DC2626",
                      "content": "01",
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 12,
                      "fontWeight": "700",
                      "letterSpacing": 0.6
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "drQtF",
                      "fill": "#0F172A",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "BOLOGNESE MEGA-BATCH (M02 + M07).  DICE 1 onion. BROWN 1.5 lb ground beef in a Dutch oven with onion + minced garlic. ADD 3 cans diced tomatoes + 2 cans tomato paste + S+P+garlic powder. SIMMER on low 45–60 min, stirring occasionally.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.55,
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 12.5,
                      "fontWeight": "500"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "L95uTP",
                  "name": "ph1s2",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "gap": 14,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "FV040",
                      "fill": "#DC2626",
                      "content": "02",
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 12,
                      "fontWeight": "700",
                      "letterSpacing": 0.6
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "x9JE9",
                      "fill": "#0F172A",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "TURKEY CHILI (M05).  In a separate pot, DICE 1 onion. BROWN 2 lb ground turkey with onion + garlic. ADD 2 cans diced tomatoes + 1 can tomato paste + 2 cans drained black beans + 2 cans drained corn. SEASON with garlic powder + S+P. SIMMER 30 min.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.55,
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 12.5,
                      "fontWeight": "500"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "lLjtf",
              "name": "ph2",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 8,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "v8puT",
                  "fill": "#DC2626",
                  "content": "PHASE 02  ·  PROTEINS IN THE OVEN",
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 11,
                  "fontWeight": "700",
                  "letterSpacing": 1.6
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "PUluq",
                  "fill": "#64748B",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Both proteins roast at 400°F. Run them on the same rack while the simmers reduce.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.5,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 12,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "eWYUK",
                  "name": "ph2s1",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "gap": 14,
                  "padding": [
                    6,
                    0,
                    0,
                    0
                  ],
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "P6SHur",
                      "fill": "#DC2626",
                      "content": "03",
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 12,
                      "fontWeight": "700",
                      "letterSpacing": 0.6
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "TOJl1",
                      "fill": "#0F172A",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "CHICKEN BREAST (M01).  SEASON 3 lb chicken breasts with S+P+garlic powder. BAKE at 400°F for 22–25 min until 165°F internal. COOL 5 min, then DICE into bite-sized pieces.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.55,
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 12.5,
                      "fontWeight": "500"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "wnDaC",
                  "name": "ph2s2",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "gap": 14,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "Z4O54",
                      "fill": "#DC2626",
                      "content": "04",
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 12,
                      "fontWeight": "700",
                      "letterSpacing": 0.6
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "L1dO54",
                      "fill": "#0F172A",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "SALMON (M03).  SEASON 4 salmon portions with soy sauce + honey + minced garlic. BAKE at 400°F from frozen for 18–20 min.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.55,
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 12.5,
                      "fontWeight": "500"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "ZUsqx",
              "name": "ph3",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 8,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "j1GO6E",
                  "fill": "#DC2626",
                  "content": "PHASE 03  ·  STIR-FRY + CURRY PAN",
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 11,
                  "fontWeight": "700",
                  "letterSpacing": 1.6
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "I371D",
                  "fill": "#64748B",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "One sauté pan does double duty — stir-fry first, then the curry. The 5.5 lb stir-fry blend splits evenly between M04 and M06.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.5,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 12,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "A2OkVR",
                  "name": "ph3s1",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "gap": 14,
                  "padding": [
                    6,
                    0,
                    0,
                    0
                  ],
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "SlJQ4",
                      "fill": "#DC2626",
                      "content": "05",
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 12,
                      "fontWeight": "700",
                      "letterSpacing": 0.6
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "ANOM3",
                      "fill": "#0F172A",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "STIR-FRY CHICKEN (M04).  SLICE 2.5 lb chicken tenderloins into strips. STIR-FRY in avocado oil with garlic + soy sauce until cooked through.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.55,
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 12.5,
                      "fontWeight": "500"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "n66dvE",
                  "name": "ph3s2",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "gap": 14,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "DltLL",
                      "fill": "#DC2626",
                      "content": "06",
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 12,
                      "fontWeight": "700",
                      "letterSpacing": 0.6
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "p7hxU4",
                      "fill": "#0F172A",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "STIR-FRY VEG (M04).  In the same pan, COOK ~2.75 lb of the stir-fry blend (half the bag) with soy sauce + garlic. SET aside with the chicken.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.55,
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 12.5,
                      "fontWeight": "500"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "nkiPY",
                  "name": "ph3s3",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "gap": 14,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "k3Vc4p",
                      "fill": "#DC2626",
                      "content": "07",
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 12,
                      "fontWeight": "700",
                      "letterSpacing": 0.6
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "YNG0M",
                      "fill": "#0F172A",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "SHRIMP (M06).  THAW 2 lb shrimp. QUICK-SAUTÉ in coconut oil with garlic until pink — 3 min. SET aside.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.55,
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 12.5,
                      "fontWeight": "500"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "YuukR",
                  "name": "ph3s4",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "gap": 14,
